description:
Is it time to rebuild Gods house, the church? Are we doing the work? Or have we, like the Jews in Haggais day, become comfortable in our daily lives, unwilling to make the effort? Haggai 2 shows that its easier to be made unclean than to be made clean. How can the church be sanctified?

In this typological Bible study on the book of Haggai, Walter Veith applies lessons to Gods remnant church. Discover answers to your questions on sanctification, righteousness by faith, perfectionism, liberalism, antinomianism, and salvation in this study of the book of Haggai.

http://amazingdiscoveries.tv/media/1185/1013-haggai-a-call-to-sanctification/
